ects blank for now and fill them in during play.%0a%3c %0a%3c ---•  %0a%3c %0a---%0a> - Characters start at a Submerged power level: 10 Refresh, 35 skill points, and a Superb (+5) skill cap.%0a> %0a> - The Phase 4 & 5 Guest Star aspects are not required for sanctioning. You may choose to leave these aspects blank for now and fill them in during play.%0a> %0a> ---- %0a> %0a68,69c68,69%0a%3c •  The consolidated skills have all the trappings of both skills that were merged into them. For example, PHYSIQUE is used for Breaking Things, Lifting Things, determining your capacity for physical stress, and all other trappings of Might and Endurance both.%0a%3c %0a---%0a> - The consolidated skills have all the trappings of both skills that were merged into them. For example, PHYSIQUE is used for Breaking Things, Lifting Things, determining your capacity for physical stress, and all other trappings of Might and Endurance both.%0a> %0a75,80c75,80%0a%3c •  Minor Milestones and Refreshes occur every two weeks, on Saturday.%0a%3c •  Significant Milestones occur on the first of every month.%0a%3c •  Major Milestones occur after an equinox/solstice, or after Halloween.%0a%3c %0a%3c •  All Consequences require some kind of justification to begin recovery unless a power otherwise modifies this (like Wizard’s Constitution or Recovery).%0a%3c %0a---%0a> - Minor Milestones and Refreshes occur every two weeks, on Saturday.%0a> - Significant Milestones occur on the first of every month.%0a> - Major Milestones occur after an equinox/solstice, or after Halloween.%0a> %0a> - All Consequences require some kind of justification to begin recovery unless a power otherwise modifies this (like Wizard’s Constitution or Recovery).%0a> %0a85,86c85,86%0a%3c •  Healing rules and clarifications can be found [[http://df.gamingsandbox.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=120&t=1122|here]].%0a%3c %0a---%0a> - Healing rules and clarifications can be found [[http://df.gamingsandbox.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=120&t=1122|here]].%0a> %0a94,99c94,99%0a%3c •  Mundane Armor for PCs is capped at Armor: 2 for now, except in very special circumstances. The availability of Armor: 3 may change as the game progresses. %0a%3c %0a%3c •  Mundane Weapons for PCs are capped at Weapon: 3, except in very special circumstances. The availability of Weapon:4+ weapons may change as the game progresses. Two exceptions to this are grenades, which typically are zone-wide attacks valued at Weapon: 4, or using a car as a weapon (typically Weapon: 4).%0a%3c %0a%3c •  You can increase an Item of Power’s normal weapon damage by +2 stress by including Incite Limited Potent Effect: Sharp, or Massive, or some other narratively appropriate modifier, on the IoP for -1 refresh. This boost to stress cannot be upgraded further.%0a%3c %0a---%0a> - Mundane Armor for PCs is capped at Armor: 2 for now, except in very special circumstances. The availability of Armor: 3 may change as the game progresses. %0a> %0a> - Mundane Weapons for PCs are capped at Weapon: 3, except in very special circumstances. The availability of Weapon:4+ weapons may change as the game progresses. Two exceptions to this are grenades, which typically are zone-wide attacks valued at Weapon: 4, or using a car as a weapon (typically Weapon: 4).%0a> %0a> - You can increase an Item of Power’s normal weapon damage by +2 stress by including Incite Limited Potent Effect: Sharp, or Massive, or some other narratively appropriate modifier, on the IoP for -1 refresh. This boost to stress cannot be upgraded further.%0a> %0a104,113c104,113%0a%3c •  We use the optional Escalation rules for Compels, where a GM may escalate a particularly important compel by offering a second or even third Fate Point against the same Aspect. This is not the same as compelling multiple aspects at once; an Escalated compel must be accepted in full or paid off in full (with the same amount of FPs paid to the GM as offered by the Escalated Compel).%0a%3c %0a%3c •  We use a special set of rules for group-PC preparation mechanics, found [[http://df.gamingsandbox.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=120&t=1225|here]]. It is not necessary that you memorize them, but it is good to familiarize yourself before they show up in the middle of a scene.%0a%3c %0a%3c •  We use several optional DFRPG rules: Overflow, Success at a Cost, and Success with Style. The rules for these can be found [[http://df.gamingsandbox.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=120&t=1336|here]].%0a%3c %0a%3c •  Any time you might be capable of making a Spray Attack, you can instead opt to perform a “Spray Maneuver.” A discussion on the mechanics and explanation behind this is located [[link|here]].%0a%3c %0a%3c •  Strength powers increase the distance you can throw objects by one zone per level of Strength you have.%0a%3c %0a---%0a> - We use the optional Escalation rules for Compels, where a GM may escalate a particularly important compel by offering a second or even third Fate Point against the same Aspect. This is not the same as compelling multiple aspects at once; an Escalated compel must be accepted in full or paid off in full (with the same amount of FPs paid to the GM as offered by the Escalated Compel).%0a> %0a> - We use a special set of rules for group-PC preparation mechanics, found [[http://df.gamingsandbox.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=120&t=1225|here]]. It is not necessary that you memorize them, but it is good to familiarize yourself before they show up in the middle of a scene.%0a> %0a> - We use several optional DFRPG rules: Overflow, Success at a Cost, and Success with Style. The rules for these can be found [[http://df.gamingsandbox.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=120&t=1336|here]].%0a> %0a> - Any time you might be capable of making a Spray Attack, you can instead opt to perform a “Spray Maneuver.” A discussion on the mechanics and explanation behind this is located [[link|here]].%0a> %0a> - Strength powers increase the distance you can throw objects by one zone per level of Strength you have.%0a> %0a118,120c118,124%0a%3c •  You may be able to access Sponsor Debt without needing Sponsored Magic, provided you have a [[http://df.gamingsandbox.com/powers/view/134|Sponsored Agenda]].%0a%3c %0a%3c •  Using Lasting Effects like “fire” or “ice,” etc, in conjunction with a weapon doesn’t stack the Incite Effect damage with the item’s damage--you pick one or the other on a successful strike, whichever is more advantageous to the attacker. %0a\ No newline at end of file%0a---%0a> - You may be able to access Sponsor Debt without needing Sponsored Magic, provided you have a [[http://df.gamingsandbox.com/powers/view/134|Sponsored Agenda]].%0a> %0a> - Using Lasting Effects like “fire” or “ice,” etc, in conjunction with a weapon doesn’t stack the Incite Effect damage with the item’s damage--you pick one or the other on a successful strike, whichever is more advantageous to the attacker.  %0a> %0a> - You may take as many different types of supplemental actions as you like during a Full Action for a cumulative -1 on your roll. You cannot reduce your effective roll to below Mediocre (+0) this way. To be clear, different “types” of supplemental actions include (but are not limited to) clearing a Mild Physical Consequence with Recovery, moving a zone, picking something up, drawing or reloading a weapon, etc. %0a> %0a> - Declarations can be made as a free action at any time, but they do not come with a free tag on them unless a Fate Point was spent to create them. Declarations may be made as a Full Action in the manner of a Navel-Gazing Maneuver or Assessment, which do come with a free tag. Declarations made outside of the pressure of time come with a free tag.%0a
