diff:1453517744:1453510013:=6,7c6%0a%3c *[[#MISC|Miscellaneous Rules]]%0a%3c %0a---%0a> %0a15,16c14%0a%3c *[[http://ragnarok.gamingsandbox.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=9&t=659#p4459 | Jade Court Vampires]] are allowed.  Click %0a%3c the link for details.%0a---%0a> *[[http://ragnarok.gamingsandbox.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=9&t=659#p4459 | Jade Court Vampires]] are allowed.  Click the link for details.%0a20,27c18,24%0a%3c %0a%3c Custom White House Courts in Play Include:%0a%3c *The members of House Kassel, those who feed on Wrath.%0a%3c *The members of House Milliner, those who feed on Gluttony.%0a%3c *The members of House Peretti, those who feed on Envy.%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a---%0a> *Custom White House Courts in Play Include:%0a> **The members of House Kassel, those who feed on Wrath.%0a> **The members of House Milliner, those who feed on Gluttony.%0a> **The members of House Peretti, those who feed on Envy.%0a> %0a> %0a> %0a48,64d44%0a%3c [[#MISC]]%0a%3c !!!Miscellaneous House Rules and Links%0a%3c %0a%3c Declarations made as a free action do not come with a free tag on them unless a Fate Point was spent in their creation. Declarations made as a Full Action come with a free tag. Declarations made outside of the pressure of time come with a free tag.%0a%3c %0a%3c We use the optional Escalation rules for Compels, where a GM may Escalate a particularly important compel by offering a second or even third Fate Point against the same Aspect. This is not the same as compelling multiple aspects at once; an Escalated compel must be accepted in full or paid off in full (with the same amount of FPs paid to the GM as offered by the Escalated Compel).%0a%3c %0a%3c * Healing Rules and Clarifications can be found [[http://ragnarok.gamingsandbox.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=10&t=1149|here]].%0a%3c %0a%3c * Holy Touch has been rewritten. The new rules for it can be found [[http://ragnarok.gamingsandbox.com/powers/view/27|here]].%0a%3c %0a%3c * Several powers such as Claws and Breath Weapon have been replaced by the [[http://ragnarok.gamingsandbox.com/powers/view/89|Natural Weaponry]] power, which is intended to allow a broad range of custom abilities.%0a%3c %0a%3c * Sponsor Debt may be taken to aid any roll (not just spells) that falls in line with the Sponsor’s Agenda, as approved by the GM. %0a%3c %0a%3c * Consequences recover according to [[http://ragnarok.gamingsandbox.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=10&t=165|this]] article.%0a%3c %0a68,83c48,62%0a%3c Based on the book's use of emotion, pain, and other "aspects" to fuel magic, a clarification is in order. You may use maneuvers/declarations/other aspects for your magic, if it makes sense. You can't use the Scene's [Dank and Wet] aspect to make a firebomb, for example, or use your [Enraged] emotion to stay hidden. You may even tag or invoke an appropriate aspect for effect to cast “free” 1-stress spells without taking Mental Stress (which may be boosted further with other tags/invokes as appropriate; Rotes cannot be cast when covering Mental Stress this way).%0a%3c %0a%3c * Official Summoning rules can be found [[http://ragnarok.gamingsandbox.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=10&t=847|here]].%0a%3c %0a%3c * Official Shapeshifting rules can be found [[http://ragnarok.gamingsandbox.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=10&t=848|here]].%0a%3c %0a%3c * We use the Soulfire rules found in the Paranet Papers, with some clarifications, found [[http://ragnarok.gamingsandbox.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=10&t=1190|here]].%0a%3c %0a%3c * Evocation Blocks and Counterspells have some modifications/specifications that can be found [[http://ragnarok.gamingsandbox.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=10&t=948|here]] and [[http://ragnarok.gamingsandbox.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=10&t=990|here]].%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c Thaumaturgy, Evothaum, and Enchanted Items/Potions containing Thaumaturgic spells may be used to string more than one aspect together into one maneuver. Each aspect's strength must be appropriately powerful and is considered separate from the others, so if you cast a spell at a target that had one aspect at 3, another at 4, and another at 5, and the target rolls the 4 to defend you have a failure, a "fragile," and one based on the power for duration. You may also "spray" these aspects at multiple targets.%0a%3c %0a%3c * In the above paragraph, "fragile" is in quotes because magical maneuvers are not fragile; all are considered sticky and last until their duration ends.%0a%3c %0a%3c * Invokes/compels used to boost potion strength cannot boost a potion beyond a casting strength of twice your Lore, much in the same way an Enchanted Item's maximum strength is twice your Lore.%0a---%0a> *Based on the book's use of emotion, pain, and other "aspects" to fuel magic, a clarification is in order. You may use maneuvers/declarations/other aspects for your magic, if it makes sense. You can't use the Scene's [Dank and Wet] aspect to make a firebomb, for example, or use your [Enraged] emotion to stay hidden. You may even tag or invoke an appropriate aspect for effect to cast “free” 1-stress spells without taking Mental Stress (which may be boosted further with other tags/invokes as appropriate; Rotes cannot be cast when covering Mental Stress this way).%0a> %0a> [[http://ragnarok.gamingsandbox.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=10&t=948|Reactionary Blocks]] and [[http://ragnarok.gamingsandbox.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=10&t=990|reactionary Counterspells]] are allowed as part of Channeling/Evocation without a stunt.%0a> %0a> *Official Summoning rules can be found [[http://ragnarok.gamingsandbox.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=10&t=847|here]].%0a> *Official Shapeshifting rules can be found [[http://ragnarok.gamingsandbox.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=10&t=848|here]].%0a> %0a> *Thaumaturgy, Evothaum, and Enchanted Items containing Thaumaturgic spells may string more than one aspect together into one maneuver. Each aspect's strength must be appropriately powerful and is considered separate from the others, so if you cast a spell at a target that had one aspect at 3, another at 4, and another at 5, and the target rolls the 4 to defend you have a failure, a "fragile," and one based on the power for duration. You may also "spray" these aspects at multiple targets.%0a> %0a> *In the above paragraph, "fragile" is in quotes because magical maneuvers are not fragile; all are considered sticky and last until their duration ends.%0a> %0a> *Invokes/compels used to boost potion strength cannot boost a potion beyond a casting strength of twice your Lore, much in the same way an Enchanted Item's maximum strength is twice your Lore.%0a> %0a> !!!Healing Rules%0a> *Healing Rules and Clarifications can be found [[http://ragnarok.gamingsandbox.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=10&t=1149|here]].%0a
