diff:1405742160:1399772714:=9a10,17%0a> Make your character proactive. A proactive character investigates strange happenings, helps people in trouble, and otherwise goes out and does things that create story. A good part of the game comes from interacting with other PCs, so give your character reasons to go out and interact with others! The less work it takes to get your character involved, the more fun you'll have.%0a> %0a> Your character is part of a large ensemble cast. This doesn't mean your character won't get a chance to shine, but it does mean you'll need to be comfortable with giving other characters time in the spotlight. Think of it as the difference between Iron Man and The Avengers. The Avengers isn't focused on Tony Stark the way Iron Man is - sometimes he isn't on the screen at all - but he still gets to have some amazing heroic moments. So does the Hulk. So does Thor. So does Black Widow. You get the idea. The Avengers is about the team, not just a single member.%0a> %0a> Give your character's aspects clear phrasing. Due to the nature of chat games, your GMs won't always have time to read through the history of every character in their scenes. Your character's aspects should speak for themselves. If no one understands what they mean or what they say, they won't get used that often. Say what you mean so it's clear to someone who is just reading the aspect itself. You can be creative and poetic, but don't be too metaphoric or you'll confuse people.%0a> %0a> Create a character that's fun and engaging to play, even when there's nothing dramatic going on. Ragnarok NYC is always on, which means the game is still running even when all the GMs are offline. Think about what your character does when there isn't anything supernatural happening, and make sure you'll still have fun roleplaying those moments. You'll get the most out of the game if your character is enjoyable to play even without GM intervention.%0a> %0a12d19%0a%3c *All Templates and Powers in Your Story are allowed.%0a25,26c32,33%0a%3c Characters start at 12 Refresh, 40 skill points. Skills at Fantastic (+6) are allowed at character creation.%0a%3c %0a---%0a> Characters start at 11 Refresh, 40 skill points. Skills at Fantastic (+6) are allowed at character creation.%0a> %0a32,34c39,41%0a%3c * Endurance and Might have been consolidated into Physique%0a%3c * Fists and Weapons have been consolidated into Fight%0a%3c %0a---%0a> Endurance and Might have been consolidated into Physique%0a> Fists and Weapons have been consolidated into Fight%0a> %0a46,55d52%0a%3c %0a%3c !!!Character Creation Advice%0a%3c %0a%3c Make your character proactive. A proactive character investigates strange happenings, helps people in trouble, and otherwise goes out and does things that create story. A good part of the game comes from interacting with other PCs, so give your character reasons to go out and interact with others! The less work it takes to get your character involved, the more fun you'll have.%0a%3c %0a%3c Your character is part of a large ensemble cast. This doesn't mean your character won't get a chance to shine, but it does mean you'll need to be comfortable with giving other characters time in the spotlight. Think of it as the difference between Iron Man and The Avengers. The Avengers isn't focused on Tony Stark the way Iron Man is - sometimes he isn't on the screen at all - but he still gets to have some amazing heroic moments. So does the Hulk. So does Thor. So does Black Widow. You get the idea. The Avengers is about the team, not just a single member.%0a%3c %0a%3c Give your character's aspects clear phrasing. Due to the nature of chat games, your GMs won't always have time to read through the history of every character in their scenes. Your character's aspects should speak for themselves. If no one understands what they mean or what they say, they won't get used that often. Say what you mean so it's clear to someone who is just reading the aspect itself. You can be creative and poetic, but don't be too metaphoric or you'll confuse people.%0a%3c %0a%3c Create a character that's fun and engaging to play, even when there's nothing dramatic going on. Ragnarok NYC is always on, which means the game is still running even when all the GMs are offline. Think about what your character does when there isn't anything supernatural happening, and make sure you'll still have fun roleplaying those moments. You'll get the most out of the game if your character is enjoyable to play even without GM intervention.%0a
